  "prompt": "What are good, low-cost (or free) alternatives to Google Alerts?",
  "response": "Here are several good alternatives to Google Alerts:\n\nFree Options:\n1. Talkwalker Alerts\n- Similar to Google Alerts\n- Monitors web, news, blogs, forums\n- Email notifications\n\n2. Social Mention\n- Real-time social media monitoring\n- Free platform\n- Tracks mentions across social platforms\n\n3. Mention\n- Basic free plan available\n- Monitors web and social media\n- Multiple language support\n\n4. News Now\n- Free news monitoring\n- Aggregates news from multiple sources\n- Customizable alerts\n\n5. Feedly\n- RSS feed reader\n- Track topics and keywords\n- Free basic version\n\nLow-Cost Options:\n1. Brand24\n- Comprehensive social media monitoring\n- Affordable pricing\n- Detailed analytics\n\n2. Hootsuite\n- Social media monitoring\n- Tracking and reporting\n- Affordable plans\n\n3. Buffer\n- Social media tracking\n- Some free features\n- Reasonably priced plans\n\n4. Google Trends\n- Free trend tracking\n- Keyword research\n- Insights into search volume\n\n5. Microsoft Alerts\n- Similar to Google Alerts\n- Part of Bing search ecosystem\n- Free to use\n\nEach platform has unique features, so compare them to find the best fit for your needs.",
